The standalone versions of confluence have always used relative paths for the installer.  This is great if you want to make a backup, or to do some testing of the new version while the current version is running by allowing you to rename the root directory for the install without breaking anything (or to use a symbolic link for your services that points to the current version).  

The installer, however, uses absolute paths for everything instead of the relative paths meaning that we're now stuck with /home/confluence/confluence-4.0.3/ in our path which is (a) problematic because it's not that version and (b) because it can only run from that path.  The standalone installer demonstrates that the system can run perfectly well without the absolute paths, is it possible to make the installer work this way? This would provide a lot more flexibility as a sysadmin.

